    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_no.00124_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Farringford,</name>
                    <name type="place">Freshwater,</name>
                    <name type="place">Isle of Wight.</name>
                    <date when="1892-01-26"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Jan 26/92</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>For Mr Walt Whitman</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>My father<ptr target="n0625"/> thanks you cordially for yr new edition of 'Leaves of Grass'&#8212;He 
                is not allowed by his doctors to write more than is absolutely necessary&#8212;We 
                are very sorry to hear that you have been unwell but hope
                that&#8212;as the spring advances&#8212;your health
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_no.00126_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_no.00128_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_no.00129_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="loc_no.00127_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                will improve.</p>
            <p>With my greetings for the New Year.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yr faithfully</salute>
                <signed>Hallam Tennyson</signed> 
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="loc_no.00125_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="authorial" place="left">To Walt Whitman</note>
        </body>
